thread.title: Northpoint improves to 9-0; Central edges past Southwind
thread.title_full: Northpoint improves to 9-0; Central edges past Southwind

author: John Varlas
title: Northpoint improves to 9-0; Central edges past Southwind
text:
Related Coverage Northpointâ€™s stout defense stops Harding Central holds on to beat Southwind Week 9 prep football roundup Prep football scores and summaries from Oct. 16 In a season with plenty of offense, Northpoint and Harding got together for an old-fashioned defensive struggle Friday.
And the Trojans came out on top, holding the Lions scoreless on three trips inside the red zone to win 12-7 . Northpoint, which is ranked ninth in the Dandy Dozen , improved to 9-0 and wrapped up the regular season Division 2-A West Region title. The Trojans and Munford, which beat Overton on Thursday, remain the only undefeated teams in the Memphis area.
Christian Saulsberry (13 yards) and Nelson Fabrizius (11) had touchdown runs for Northpoint. Harding (6-2) didn't get into the end zone until Marquavious Moore scored on a 9-yard run with 2:13 to go in the game.
Central threw the Region 8-5A standings into even more of a jumble, rallying to defeat Dandy Dozen No. 8 Southwind, 30-28 . The result leaves Central, Southwind and Kirby tied for third in the league behind Munford and Brighton, with only the top four teams making the playoffs.
MUS and CBHS will meet for the Division 2-AA West Region championship in two weeks after victories.
The third-ranked Owls (6-2) got three touchdowns from Memphis commitment Thomas Pickens to defeat Briarcrest 31-12. CBHS (6-2) got 238 yards and three touchdowns from Austin Lee and two touchdown runs and a touchdown pass from Keegan Voss in a 49-13 victory over St. Benedict.
Chase Hayden ran for 178 yards on just eight carries and scored four touchdowns as No. 10 St. George's ran past Tipton-Rosemark, 73-7.
